==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Processionary
<hw>Pro*ces"sion*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<ets>processionarius</ets>, F. <ets>processionnaire</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to a procession; consisting in processions; <as>as,
<ex>processionary</ex> service</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Processionary moth</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any
moth of the genus <gen>Cnethocampa</gen>, especially <spn>Cnethocampa
processionea</spn> of Europe, whose larv⟦ae⟧ make large webs on oak
trees, and go out to feed in regular order. They are covered with
stinging hairs.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Processioner</ent>⟦br⟧
